        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 7:53PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 753 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Whitewater, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Whitewater, Saco, Hinsdale, St. Marie, Vandalia, Thoeny, Sleeping
Buffalo, and Frenchman Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
